text: Avellan Capital Avellan Capital is an investment firm specializing in public stocks in TMT sector in the United States and Western Our key focus is on growing companies with proven business models and clear expansion The small size allows us to invest in promising companies of $100-1,000m market capitalization where big funds don t find enough liquidity and small ones have limited research talent to assess companiesâ growth We use a research intensive, focused investment approach and conduct the fundamental analysis to select our We generally invest in companies based on a thorough assessment of their business models and fundamentals, the quality of their management teams, cyclical and secular industry trends and macro Our goal is to provide performance for our investors, and the key asset in achieving it is our We retain detail oriented and curious individuals with a robust knowledge of corporate finance and the ability to leave no stone untouched in their For inquiries

PPC Management Services by Landscapers Web Marketing Home About Us Our Strategy Our Services Website Design & Development SEO PPC Social Media Marketing Reputation Management Email, SMS, & Marketing Automation Industries Sprinklers & Irrigations Hardscape & Outdoor Living Arborists & Tree Services Landscape Design Outdoor Lighting Turf & Lawn Care Resources News & Media Training Video Training Monthly Magazine Podcast Contact Us Menu Home About Us Our Strategy Our Services Website Design & Development SEO PPC Social Media Marketing Reputation Management Email, SMS, & Marketing Automation Industries Sprinklers & Irrigations Hardscape & Outdoor Living Arborists & Tree Services Landscape Design Outdoor Lighting Turf & Lawn Care Resources News & Media Training Video Training Monthly Magazine Podcast Contact Us (844) PPC Home » Our Services » PPC Advertising for Landscapers In the world of digital marketing, results are what truly matter, and for most companies, results mean a clear increase in their return on investment (ROI). Anyone in the digital marketing industry knows that Search Engine Optimization (SEO) is the optimal way to get your website noticed by the search engines, rank higher in the Search Engine Results Pages (SERPs), and attract more potential clients to your However, SEO takes time for tangible evidence of an increased ROI to manifest In the meantime, there is a temporary way to get your website and brand in front of the customers who are looking for you right now: advertising (PPC). Advertising for Landscaping Companies Although waiting for organic traffic to increase after investing in a thoroughly planned SEO strategy can be difficult, it is well worth In the business world, though, it is sometimes necessary to get a jumpstart on the process in order to stay ahead of the If other landscapers in your area have already invested in SEO for their website, you need a way to keep up with This means you need to appear in the search results even though your SEO campaign has not yet While you are waiting for your landscaping website’s optimization to be completed and fully take effect (it may take up to 6 months for Google and other search engines to “crawl” your website and see the updates), you can invest in a advertising campaign that puts your website in the sponsored section of the PPC is the perfect way to grab the attention of clients who are looking for your landscaping services now, but you must remember that it should not be your What is Advertising? In order to generate leads – those people who are looking to invest in your products or services at the moment – some companies choose to use a marketing technique known as These are paid promotions whereby each time one of your PPC ads is clicked, you will pay a fee, and a potential client is sent to your website It is important that your PPC ad campaign is crafted for conversions since you are paying a fee for each click that your ad A paid click which simply results in a potential customer bouncing back to the previous website would be a waste of their time and your money, so it is essential that PPC ads are targeted and When investing in a PPC ad campaign, there is far more research and strategy involved than you may have It is not as simple as slapping together an ad for your landscaping business and hoping it To get your ads in front of the right potential clients, you have to know exactly where they are, what they are looking for, and how best to target them to ensure the ad is A generalized PPC ad campaign with a broad audience will either result in you running out of money because of too many false leads and unsubstantiated clicks or your ad being ignored because your audience has seen more ads like this one than they care to For the leads and conversions you want (the objective of a good PPC campaign), you must know who your audience is and where they spend their time Channels such as Google AdWords, Bing Advertising, and social media outlets such as Facebook and Instagram can be used for PPC The most critical part of the PPC ad is that it has a specific target who is most interested in your landscaping Your ads must include keywords which have been successful throughout your SEO campaigns, copy that is pertinent and straightforward, and links which send potential clients to the right landing This will provide you with the best possible chance that they will contact you or complete whatever call to action you are hoping they will Grow Your Landscaping Business with Advertising Campaigns The best way to increase traffic to your website and work to convert visitors into actual clients is through expert Search Engine However, in the time it takes for SEO to take effect, you may need to invest in a temporary PPC advertising campaign to boost your rankings and get your website in front of the clients who need your landscaping services right It is a great method of keeping up with your competition until your website begins to rank and bri

Wash & Learn Wash & Learn – HoliFrog Skip to content Close menu Shop Wash & Learn Skintellect™ Situational Cleansing™ About Log in Facebook Instagram Cart Close cart : Orders may have processing & shipping delays | Enjoy free shipping on orders $70+ Search Site navigation Shop Wash & Learn Skintellect™ Situational Cleansing™ About Log in Search Cart Search "Close (esc)" Wash & Learn Pore Behavior So we’ve all got They’re supposed to release stuff out of our skin, but sometimes they hoard stuff that finds its way in there from the environment and anything else that happens to come into contact with your Pores are tiny, relatively speaking, so they’re tricky to They do a pretty good job of keeping themselves tidy, but if you’re wearing makeup, touching your face a lot, or you live in a place with air quality or a harsh climate, they’re going to need your help to stay and That’s where your face wash comes in — ideally one that only uses safe and effective Using products with gross, harmful stuff in them? Well, that’s just There are enough toxic influences in your life without rubbing them directly onto your We all have our Safe and ingredients should be ground zero of So, here we Cleanser Counts Washing your face is usually not the sort of thing you It’s just another step in between brushing your teeth and showering, or whatever order your daily hygiene falls You may not give it much thought at all — after all, your facial cleanser just makes a quick cameo, sudsing up your mug and then there it goes, down the drain in a But during this brief and very important period is when the foundation of your skincare regimen begins, setting your skin up for the rest of what’s to All those expensive serums and creams you splurged on can’t give you the glowing, radiant skin of a newborn babe they promised unless they’re working on a properly cleansed, fresh canvas: AKA your face with absolutely nothing on Anything less is like making a salad without washing the leaves first (we’ll let you imagine those potential consequences). Cleanser counts, big Indulge Your Cravings You know how there are skin types? Makes sense that there should be cleanser types, too then, right? isn’t going to cut it when there’s skin in the game (literally). Whether your skin falls under dry, oily, combo, or “normal,” all those skin cells turn over just the same like seasons repeating themselves, so your routine should keep When your face is feeling congested and dull, something with a gentle exfoliant will help shimmy those microscopic dead skin flakes away, revealing smooth baby skin If it’s parched, you’ll need something a bit more pampering to keep things plush and And when your pores are evicting sebum like it’s going out of business, that’s when the extra elbow grease is (And yes, you do, in fact, fight oil with oil — more on that ) We’ve all got cravings and so does our But you should actually listen to your skin’s. Clean Smarter, Not Harder If you want your skin to look its best, you have to wash your Every day . We don’t make the rules that’s just how the game is A couple tenets: don’t rush, don’t scrub too hard, and don’t forget your But what about makeup? Longwear foundation and waterproof mascara is a modern triumph, and removing it can feel more arduous than getting houseguests to take the hint when they’re overstaying their That’s when Kissimmee Vitamin F Therapy Balmy Wash comes in — think of it like a or a makeup remover that won’t tear your poor little eyelashes out like a face wipe or cotton pad will Massage it onto dry skin until it emulsifies with your makeup and then rinse away and move onto your next choice of cleanser to whisk away remaining Congratulations, you’ve just In the mornings when the only thing on your face is lingering sleep and pillow dust, feel free to start your day with any of our three other cleansers: Tashmoo Water Lily Nourishing Milky Wash for those with dry and or sensitive skin, Superior Omega Nutritive Gel Wash for a refreshing , or Shasta AHA Refining Acid Wash for a thorough pore Feel free to rotate accordingly, morning and Contact Shipping & Returns Press FAQ Holilands™ Stores Privacy Policy Don’t sell your soul for good skin sign up for Less Enter your email SIGN UP Connect with us! crappie fishing can be outstanding in Midwestern That s very true on Lake of the Ozarks as winter Crappie tend to "school up" and cooperate with Though one can certainly find crappie schools in open water, in the interest of time and consistency, we usually target crappie around larger condo docks in deep water that offer crappie cover, shade, bait fish, and ambush We typically utilize side scan to locate crappie schools and switch to forward facing sonar to present our baits to fish accurately and In terms of gear, we prefer to target winter crappie with an ultralight rod and reel spooled with pound test Its been my experience that 4 pound line will outperform 6 pound line in terms of number of bites and fish caught in clear We generally use inch Jigs in natural colors on a 1 16 ounce jig Since late summer I ve been using a variety of jig styles and colors from "Ol Blue Tackle" with good Their Slapper and Squid jig bodies have been quite productive for our guides and Depending on the day, one may have to experiment with jig color, style, jig head weight, retrieve speed, scent attractants and other variables to optimize your catch, but that s part of crappie At times scent attractants such as Crappie Niblets (Pink or Chartreuse) and Hawg Jam can improve one s catch and we routinely use A few tips for winter anglers: Dress in layers for comfort, wear your life jacket, bring a dry blanket and extra clothes in the boat, fish with a buddy, check for ice on the boat ramps before attempting to launch your boat, and lookout for navigational hazards such as patches of ice, floating debris, Consequences of on the water mishaps or mistakes are significantly elevated when the water temp drops in the We hope to see you on the water soon and wish you a safe, enjoyable, and productive winter! 0 Comments Fall Crappie Fishing on Lake of the Ozarks! 1 2023 0 Comments Lake of the Ozarks surface temperature is unseasonably warm for early (78-80 degrees) That means we re finding and catching Crappie in feet of water in or around deep brush When the water starts cooling, Crappie and other fish species will move up in the water One must adapt their tactics and approach to lake conditions to be Thanks to the excellent sonar imaging technology available today, its far easier to locate and catch fish than it was years In addition to water temperature, water clarity plays a significant role in where and how one should pursue Right now, not only is Lake of the Ozarks unusually warm, it is also very clear due to a lack of rainfall and the fish are deep or under A ring light is a circular lamp or flash that surrounds the lens of a This produces even lighting, diffused shadows and a cool in the subject s (If you ve seen yourself in a lighted makeup mirror, that s a ring light ) Beauty vloggers on Instagram and YouTube have long used ring lights to add professional polish to makeup tutorials (and to reduce the appearance of wrinkles). Similarly, YouTube and Twitch streamers often use a ring light as part of an inexpensive lighting Nevertheless, the ring light has become an increasingly useful tool in the modern social distancing Ring Lights for Zoom Meetings Ring lights are a way to improve lighting in a home office or work from home “Initially, daylight or room light may have been sufficient, but if the next few months require regular videoconference appearances, then looking professional and ensuring that facial expressions and body language are visible is important to communicate effectively,” advises Natalia Vander Laan, , a A ring light also pairs well with a green screen backdrop . A typical kit includes a stand and colored Some kits also include a carrying case, phone holder and a These holders and stands are often made of lightweight plastic and shouldn’t be trusted to hold expensive cameras or How Much Does a Good Ring Light Cost? A good ring light (with verified, reviews) costs approximately $55, according to a analysis of price Those same lighting kits cost around $42 while on sale: an average discount of %. adults, young, old, or , have and carefully considered estate and incapacity planning These documents ensure that (1) your loved ones have the proper paperwork and documentation to be able to handle your affairs and make decisions for you upon your death or incapacity and (2) that YOU choose who serves in specific roles for We recommend that you have three very important documents in place (1) an Advance Directive for Health Care, (2) a Durable Financial Power of Attorney, and (3) a Last Will & The Advance Directive for Health Care and Durable Power of Attorney are incapacity planning documents and dictate who will be making key decisions for you in the event that you are still living but The Last Will & Testament is your estate planning document and dictates who is in charge of your estate, who is serving in certain roles, and how your property is distributed after your For some of our clients we use Trusts (both revocable and irrevocable) as their estate planning documents to accomplish other goals such as asset protection or avoiding Our attorneys can help you put together your estate plan to protect yourself, your loved ones, and ensure your property is distributed in A guardian is granted custody and control over an incapacitated individual by the Probate Guardians are responsible for making sure the ward has adequate medical attention, an acceptable place to live, adequate food, In Georgia, any “interested person” may file a petition for the appointment of himself or some other qualified person as guardian of an incapacitated person, and if so appointed by the judge, may serve in that An “interested person” is an individual who has an interest in the welfare of an incapacitated person, and is not himself a minor, ward, or protected What is Conservatorship? A conservator is granted control over financial matters for an incapacitated individual, such as paying their bills, filing taxes, determining a budget for the ward, taking care of the ward’s investments, A conservator has no authority to make decisions regarding the ward’s personal In Georgia, guardianship and conservatorship is the process by which an individual seeks appointment through the court as official legal representative of another Once a guardian and or conservator is appointed for someone, then that person’s legal right to make significant decisions has been Petitioning to become a conservator or guardian can be a complex and process, and few peo

Terry Stephens August , Character and Integrity Terry Stephens August , Character is like a tree and reputation like a The shadow is what we think of it the tree is the real ( Abraham Lincoln ) Their definitions have evolved overtime, but character is how we respond to circumstances, and integrity is the way in which we I was first introduced to Jason Jones at United Throughout my career, I have had the opportunity to work with many young managers as they tackle their first It didn’t take long for me to understand that Jason was something I saw in Jason the qualities that you can’t teach from a book -- values that come from a solid foundation, qualities of his personality shaped over many years built and influenced by the people and events most important to He was different, he was aware and understood the lessons of his I watched him put those qualities to work as he took The one standing order, “Right or wrong make a decision, the worst thing you can do is just stand ” He called me every evening at 5:30 to check in and go over his list for the day, discussing each item in detail, offering a solution to each The strategic thinking is what astonished His understanding that every decision would affect his team, the project, the company, and the owner tomorrow, next week, next month, and next Jason was graceful in his ability to communicate with his team and the project stakeholders, making them understand the complexity of the projects and what was needed to bring them to a successful Jason had a talent for doing what he was doing, being a Jason and I still have our daily talk, now it’s at 5:30 in the morning over It’s more about building a company these days than building a The more mornings we meet, the more we understand that the two are not that different a well thought out plan, execution of the plan by a productive team, and do it with character and It is with pleasure that I announce Jason Jones as Director of Operations of Terry Stephens February , WWBD? CLIENTS | EA Creative Parka uses hyperlocal marketing to allow brands and retail to engage with people as they roam the Recently, EA Creative helped Parka prepare for a round of fundraising meetings and Impact Streamlined pitch deck for investors and other potential partners Connected Parka’s founding team to business partners Facilitated introductions to VC and PE firms Continuing to assist with strategic planning on an ongoing basis Services Strategic planning, partnerships, creative communications, creative direction clients HOME ABOUT SERVICES TEAM CLIENTS PROFILES CONTACT More EA Creative   PROFILES | EA Creative All Posts Women s History Month EA Creative Jun 8 Women in Leadership Q&A with Talia Kovacs Talia Kovacs CEO Litlife ​ EA Creative’s Women in Leadership conversation series recently connected Chief members Talia Kovacs with Sandhya and artwork by Eunjoo Byeon , an graphic designer and frequent Through interviews and artwork we are committed to showcasing women in leadership positions who are making history Please send us a message on Linkedin, us , and share socially to nominate someone in your Sandhya : Where do you work and what is your current role there? Talia Kovacs: I am the CEO at LitLife, an international literacy consulting firm specializing in literacy We partner with school districts in countries to make sure teachers are empowered to teach joyful, purposeful, reading and writing ​ Sandhya : What was a defining moment in your career which has led to your current role? Talia : LitLife was at a crossroads, we had to figure out how to continue to serve our students while ensuring that the company remained stable and I began our internal systems organizing as the EVP of I continued running the team and systems as COO, then the owners were looking to step away and asked me to step up and run the I became LitLife’s CEO at years old with a background as a teacher and a I quickly learned that the role difference between CEO and COO is very COO you have to ensure the ship is running, but you’re not as responsible for strategy decisions and long term As CEO, I had to make sure that all of the systems I implemented as COO continued, and also steer LitLife in a very uncertain time in education with budget cuts and the many competing priorities of school ​ Sandhya: When was a time in your career where it was clear that being a woman made your job more difficult? Are there any times it was easier? Talia : As the CEO of LitLife, I went to this meeting with two very seasoned sales I could tell when they walked in that I wasn’t being taken They gave me a ludicrous offer that no one with even a day of experience would I told them I needed to reschedule, and at the next meeting I brought in a board member who is a former education This board member also happens to be an older Once he sat down, all of a sudden everyone had much more reasonable offers to make and the tone completely I was really disappointed that that’s what it took but also knew to use all the tools at my disposal for the betterment of the ​ Sandhya: Have you had a mentor or sponsor who has helped you in your career, and how did they do that? How have you been able to do the same for someone else? Talia : Yes, I have been working with Pam Allyn, LitLife’s founder and owner, for over I met her after I came back from working for half a year in West Africa learning more about their education She had recently started a called LitWorld , focused on international Together, we created profiles of the schools I worked with in Ghana and Togo to better serve their From then on I was inspired to work alongside her, building a , empowered world for After my time teaching and as a curriculum writer, I came to work for her at LitLife and have been with this company ever Pam is a visionary leader who is always pushing me to think bigger, be bold, (that is her favorite piece of advice!) and never accept anything less than the most magical curriculum and imaginative lessons to be put in front of ​ Sandhya: Who is a historic or living woman that has inspired you? Talia : I have two - Zora Neale Hurston and Gloria I often think of these , , women together because they are both storytellers and have exemplified the importance of not only telling their own stories but amplifying the voices of those around them as ​ Sandhya: Is there something you would say to your younger self? Talia : Your career is a series of You’ll be able to keep focus on the kids no matter ​ Sandhya: What haven’t we asked you that we should and what would your answer be? Talia : As a former teacher running a business, I make it my mission to speak about the importance of running a I want other people to know that you can run a , profitable Many people who work hard to improve the lives of those around them often think of themselves as “not a business leader” - but I always want to push that narrative and emphasize that if there were more , business leaders, the world would be a bett

Introducing Entière – A New Experience for Skin Health – Entière Dermatology About Entière Mission Meet Our Doctors Your Skin Home Our Services Medical Dermatology Cosmetic Dermatology L’Entière Aesthetics Lounge Book an Appointment In The News Entière Dossier Contact Your Visit Fl 9 New York, NY Pay Your Bill our services book now pay your bill Introducing Entière – A New Experience for Skin Health Photo from: Watch and Listen September Introducing Entière – A New Experience for Skin Health In January , I stood in front of Bryon Kim’s Synedoche at the Whitney Museum of American Art in New York It is a simple but powerful depiction of unique skin tones of friends, fellow artists, strangers, and himself in rows and rows of monochrome painted I felt celebrated, comforted, and inspired from seeing the collective of skin This is the power of design and feeling inclusive in a This moment sparked the beginning of Entière . Skin is intimate but on constant As a society, we place such value on beauty and While it is superficially perceived as vanity, it actually sheds truth to how vulnerable the skin experience is and why as humans, we are so invested in As a dermatologist, I am particularly sensitive to why it can be emotional to deal with skin conditions and the natural skin changes of It is my job to care for skin diseases and conditions but we need collaboration beyond medicine, science, insurance, and medical We must examine our status We need to reach across industries to collaborate with technologists, designers, experiential strategist, and our community, in order to architect a new It took a little more than a year and a half later from the emotional experience I had at the Whitney to launch In all of our development, we stayed deliberate to inclusiveness and the entirety of how we believe the delivery of skin health should My husband actually came up with the name Entière over beers we were having at a local While neither of us speak French, we both lived in multiple countries so we were playing with words from different There is a lightness and a beauty to this French word for “whole” or “complete.” Our design process was delightfully extensive and We drew from universally grounded concepts such as basic geometry and from what skin looks like underneath the microscope, stripped of judgement, skin color, and any surface changes — but really what is in the skin We included the spectrum of skin color to appeal to everyone regardless of background, cultural influence, or life Our design is rooted in Scandinavian aesthetics due to its commitment to community and shared natural objects, such as wood and stone, since familiar elements allow people to feeling We believe that the pursuit of skin health and wellness should be democratized in a simple, beautiful, and natural approach, inspired by This is what we are doing at We invite you to join our skin health Warmly, Melissa Flourish First – Helping Employees Live Productive Lives Home page Home page Employees Who Know Their Employers . . Are More Productive Employees Every day employers lose $000s in productivity to employees who come to work worrying about personal Whether they’re struggling with their finances, with their marriage or are anxious about a problem with a child, in most cases these personal issues are affecting productivity, their coworkers and Maybe they’re concerned about navigating a major life change, or social media has convinced them they have missed out on the goodness of life that others are Studies show that each employee who disengages at work due to personal issues costs a company around $13,000 Improving employees’ personal happiness increases employee: productivity job satisfaction rates retention rates cooperation commitment and decreases: healthcare rates absenteeism What Can An Employer Do? Most employers cannot afford sufficient dedicated professional staff to provide adequate coverage for all Employee Assistance Program (EAP) solutions have focused on treating emotional, mental and substance abuse problems, but have provided very little in offering preventative solutions to help the employee before the issue became overwhelming and affected productivity, absenteeism, and Many employees are not accessing EAP’s when personal problems occur either because they aren’t comfortable going to an HR representative or a therapist or they don’t feel their problems are dire enough to warrant such a step–yet their personal issues are still draining And if EAP’s primary tool is therapy, they’re throwing a very costly and time intensive tool at most problems and taking the employee away from the job to receive the What employees want . . . % of employees want more emotional and mental health resources from their Why? % of employees with high levels of stress say they feel fatigued and out of control % of employees report that work is a significant source of stress % or employees lose 1+ hours per day due to stress Be the employer employees love to work . . Fair Play Alliance about · faq · events · members · contact About the Fair Play Alliance The Fair Play Alliance is a initiative spanning over gaming companies whose mission is to share research and best practices that drive lasting change in fostering fair play in online Mission Statement The Fair Play Alliance is a coalition of gaming professionals and companies committed to developing quality We provide an open forum for the games industry to collaborate on research and best practices that encourage fair play and healthy communities in online We envision a world where games are free of harassment, discrimination, and abuse, and where players can express themselves through FAQ What is this group about? Our goal is to share learnings for encouraging fair play and healthy communities to improve the quality of We focus on the productive (what works best to encourage team play and positive social interactions), in addition to understanding disruptive and harassing behaviour in We can work to better understand the diverse needs of players and how to deliver the best possible experiences in our We can challenge how we’ve always done We’re not going to be perfect at this, but we think we can do better by working together! What’s the problem? There are many ways to play, many perspectives on games, and many definitions of “good”. Part of what makes online games so great is playing with other people! Today, however, players are overwhelmingly telling us that they’re frustrated by how often games are disrupted, for example by on the same teams, or by harassment and Can you give some examples of what problems you’re tackling? Games can be disrupted in many ways through gameplay, exploits, cheating, misaligned goals, harassment, For example, sometimes different expectations arise about how the match should go, such as one player expecting a casual match, while another expects an intense Sometimes it’s the frustration that games can We can help find better ways to match players together who have the same goals, which improves the match and reduces the chance that you’re going to have a bad We can also help by looking for ways to lessen unnecessary friction through And there are many more We want people to enjoy playing our games, so we are also as much (if not more!) about encouraging positive play as we are about discouraging negative Why aren’t you calling this “toxicity”? “Toxicity” is an ambiguous term: it’s OK casually (we’ll use it from time to time), but it doesn’t help us accurately address the problem, which is that players feel their games are disrupted by other players too Sometimes those disruptions come about innocently (i.e. not “toxic” or with no ), sometimes they’re completely our fault because of game design or mismatched players, and sometimes it’s a player behaving way over the line, We find that “disruptive behaviour” better represents what we’re focusing on, without being too about individual expression or unfairly lumping players We want you to feel that you’re playing the matches you want to play, free of Is this all about making everyone nice on the internet? For the most part, there’s plenty room to still be ourselves, and that includes banter and trash talk where and when What we say to our friends will impact total strangers differently, particularly with the distance, lack of human signals, and pressures that can come along with communication in We hope to make interactions between players more productive not just through a better understanding of human nature, but also through game design, level design, matchmaking, and Is the goal to create a universal code of conduct? Games, communities, and individuals are all very diverse, and one blanket policy can’t cover everything without harming games in We don’t want to dictate how games should be Some games work better with cohesive, teams, some games work better with a bit more How each member chooses to apply our resources or learnings is up to What about hate and hate speech? Planificación de Recursos Empresariales (proviene del inglés: Enterprise Resource Planning). ¿Para qué sirve un Sistema ERP? Permite la gestión controlada y fluida de la empresa negocio en sus diferentes actividades internas y ¿Qué distingue a un Sistema ERP? Su principal cualidad es su capacidad de integrar diferentes módulos de gestión, propios de la actividad de una empresa negocio, en una única aplicación (ej. producción, ventas, compras, logística, contabilidad, … inventarios, pedidos, nóminas, gestión de proyectos, ). Intrega por tanto todo lo necesario para el funcionamiento de los procesos de negocio de una ¿Qué es Open ERP? OpenERP es una completa suite de negocios que incluye aplicaciones tales como: ventas, compras, CRM, proyecto, gestión de almacenes, producción, contabilidad, recursos humanos, entre Asequible, La ausencia de costos por licencia hacen de OpenERP una opción muy Los servicios que proveemos los partners y OpenERP dan gran valor al OpenERP es la única empresa que garantiza servicios de migración sin costos Modular, El enfoque modular único de OpenERP permite a los clientes iniciarse con una aplicación e ir añadiendo módulos progresivamente en el El cliente mantiene los beneficios de un software integrado pero evita los costos de un proyecto “Macro” de Flexible, OpenERP permite personalizar la interfaz de usuario, vistas de búsqueda, reportes y gestionar el proceso del negocio en pocos “clicks”. Todo lo que necesita es un navegador Nueva Generación, A diferencia de otros ERP, OpenERP esta desarrollado en nuevas tecnologías tales como Python y OpenERP se fundamenta en la potencialidad de la tecnología web proveyendo una flexibilidad Código Abierto, OpenERP esta comprometido con el desarrollo en Código El software está publicado bajo la licencia AGPL Bookmark the permalink .
